title: For Sale:  Two PRE BAN Sig Sauer P226 15 Round Magazines
location: NY State, New York, United States
postcontent:
This ad is for two Sig-Sauer P226 (9mm) factory Pre-Ban 15 round magazines.  These magazines are factory originals (not aftermarket productions)manufactured by JP Sauer before 09/13/94 and are legal to own in NY State.  You can see the visible characteristics that establish them as pre-ban magazines, such as the "dovetail" weld on the backstrap (the backstraps are now smooth), the thin metal baseplates that contain no "date-clock" stamp on the bottom (thicker plastic baseplates are manufactured now), no LE/GOVT markings on the front strap, and the "Triple J" stamp is not even on the one magazine (this is particularly unique as it predates JP Sauer's stamping of their logo on magazines, though the "Triple J" logo can be found on pre and post ban mags).  All of these characteristics combined are good indicators of pre-ban Sig-Sauer magazines.  I am asking for $37.00 for each magazine or $70.00 for both plus $6.00 for shipping, as I am located in Pittsburgh, PA.  These magazines show some light cosmetic wear for their age but are in good shape overall and function fine.  I accept Paypal for payment, or certified checks or money orders, whichever you prefer.  I ship via USPS and it usually takes about three days to NY State.  If you have any questions or would like additional photos feel free to ask.

Thanks,

Adam
